'''Ibrahim Sangaré''' (born 2 December 1997) is an Ivorian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder (association football)#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]] for {{English football updater|NottingF}} club [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] and the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tfc.info/ibrahim-sangare|title=Ibrahim Sangaré – Le site officiel du Toulouse Football Club|access-date=12 November 2016|archive-date=26 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180926085707/http://www.tfc.info/ibrahim-sangare|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==Club career==

=== Early career ===
Sangaré started his youth career with Ivorian clubs Tout Puissant Koumassi and [[AS Denguélé]].

=== Toulouse ===
Sangaré made his debut for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]] in a 0–0 draw against [[Angers SCO|Angers]] on 22 October 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lfp.fr/joueur/sangare-ibrahim-1|title=Ibrahim Sangare}}</ref>

===PSV===
On 28 September 2020, following Toulouse's [[Promotion and relegation|relegation]] to [[Ligue 2]], Sangaré joined [[Eredivisie]] club [[PSV Eindhoven]] on a five-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/news/article/sangare-strengthens-psvs-midfield.htm|title=Sangaré strengthens PSV's midfield|publisher=PSV Eindhoven|date=28 September 2020|access-date=28 September 2020|archive-date=3 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201003053008/https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/news/article/sangare-strengthens-psvs-midfield.htm|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 18 October, he made his debut for the club as a starter in a 3–0 win over [[PEC Zwolle]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=PSV Eindhoven 3–0 PEC Zwolle (Oct 18, 2020) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/574734/psv-eindhoven-pec-zwolle |access-date=2024-02-14 |publisher=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On 31 January 2021, Sangaré scored his first goal for PSV in a 3–1 loss to [[Feyenoord]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Feyenoord Rotterdam 3–1 PSV Eindhoven (Jan 31, 2021) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/574452 |access-date=2024-02-14 |publisher=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

On 3 December 2021, Sangaré was named the Eredivisie player of the month for [[2021–22 Eredivisie|November 2021]].<ref name=EPOM>{{Cite web|url=https://eredivisie.eu/news/ajax-provides-most-players-to-team-of-the-month-for-the-fourth-time/|title=Ajax provides most players to team of the month for the fourth time|date=3 December 2021|website=eredivisie.eu}}</ref> He was also included in the team of the month for October 2021<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|date=5 November 2021|title=Ajax provides most players for the team of the month for the third time|url=https://eredivisie.eu/news/ajax-provides-most-players-for-the-team-of-the-month-for-the-third-time/|url-status=live|website=eredivisie.eu|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211105135041/https://eredivisie.eu/news/ajax-provides-most-players-for-the-team-of-the-month-for-the-third-time/ |archive-date=5 November 2021 }}</ref> and December 2021 respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eredivisie.eu/news/ajax-still-provides-most-players-for-the-team-of-the-month/|title=Ajax still provides most players for team of the month|date=14 January 2022|website=eredivisie.eu}}</ref>

On 17 April 2022, Sangaré started in PSV's triumph over [[AFC Ajax–PSV Eindhoven rivalry|rivals]] [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] in the [[2022 KNVB Cup Final|KNVB Cup Final]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2425523-psv-verrast-ajax-met-twee-goals-vlak-na-rust-en-wint-knvb-beker | title=PSV verrast Ajax met twee goals vlak na rust en wint KNVB-beker|website=NOS|language=Dutch|date=17 April 2022 }}</ref>

On 7 August 2022, amid interest from several top European clubs, PSV announced that Sangaré had extended his contract with the club until 2027.<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 August 2022 |title=Sangaré extends contract with PSV until 2027 |url=https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/news/article/sangare-extends-contract-with-psv-until-2027.htm |access-date=2022-08-08 |website=psv.nl |language=en-US |archive-date=8 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220808145329/https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/news/article/sangare-extends-contract-with-psv-until-2027.htm |url-status=dead }}</ref> On 16 August 2022, Sangaré scored in a 2–2 draw away to [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] in the first leg of their [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Play-off round|UEFA Champions League]] play-off round match.<ref name=":1">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62548886|title=Rangers 2–2 PSV|publisher=BBC|date=16 August 2022|access-date=18 August 2022}}</ref> On 2 March 2023, Sangaré scored in the quarter-finals of the [[KNVB Cup]] in a 3–1 win over [[ADO Den Haag]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=PSV Eindhoven 3–1 ADO Den Haag (Mar 2, 2023) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/665803 |access-date=2024-01-17 |publisher=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> His shot registered in at 170&nbsp;km/h, making it one of the most powerful shots in recorded football history.<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 January 2024 |title=What is the hardest shot in football history? Ibrahim Sangaré scores 170km/h screamer |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/what-is-the-hardest-shot-in-football-history-ibrahim-sangare-scores-170kmh-screamer-36902233 |access-date=2024-01-17 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Hoskin |first=Rob |date=3 March 2023 |title=PSV's Ibrahim Sangaré scores incredible 170km/h screamer – the sixth hardest shot in history |url=https://www.givemesport.com/what-is-the-hardest-shot-in-football-history-ibrahimsangar-scores-170kmh-screamer/ |access-date=2024-01-17 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref> On 30 April, he started in the [[2023 KNVB Cup final|KNVB Cup final]] against [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], where after drawing 1–1 in regular and extra time, PSV won their 10th title after going 3–2 on [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalties]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=PSV Eindhoven 1–1 Ajax Amsterdam (Apr 30, 2023) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/668068 |access-date=2024-01-17 |publisher=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On 22 August, Sangaré scored in a 2–2 draw away to [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] in the first leg of their [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Play-off round|UEFA Champions League]] play-off round match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66573610|title=Rangers 2–2 PSV|publisher=BBC|date=22 August 2023|access-date=25 August 2023}}</ref>

===Nottingham Forest===
On 1 September 2023, Sangaré joined [[Premier League]] club [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] on a five-year contract,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2023/september/01/forest-complete-signing-of-ibrahim-sangar-/ |title=Forest complete signing of Ibrahim Sangaré |publisher=Nottingham Forest F.C. |date=1 September 2023 }}</ref> for £30&nbsp;million.<ref name=":2">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4827082/2023/09/01/nottingham-forest-sangare-transfer/ |title=Nottingham Forest sign Ibrahim Sangare from PSV |publisher=The Athletic |date=1 September 2023 }}</ref> On 18 September, he made his debut for the club in a 1–1 home draw against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] at the [[City Ground]].<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |title=Nottingham Forest 1–1 Burnley (Sep 18, 2023) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/671076 |access-date=2024-01-03 |publisher=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
Sangaré represented [[Ivory Coast national under-20 football team|Ivory Coast U20]] at the [[2015 Toulon Tournament]], and the [[Ivory Coast national under-23 football team|Ivory Coast U23s]] in 2 friendlies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tfc.info/ibrahim-sangare-nouvelle-recrue-estivale-du-tfc|title=Ibrahim Sangaré, nouvelle recrue estivale du TFC|access-date=12 November 2016|archive-date=8 July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160708045500/http://www.tfc.info/ibrahim-sangare-nouvelle-recrue-estivale-du-tfc|url-status=dead}}</ref>

[[File:Joueur guinéen et ivoirien 05.jpg|thumb|right|Sangaré (left) with Ivory Coast in 2024]]

On 28 December 2023, he was included in the Ivory Coast's squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] held in his home country.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.afrik-foot.com/cote-divoire-liste-can-2023-gasset-zaha-haller-pepe| title= Côte d'Ivoire : la liste pour la CAN sans Zaha, avec 2 blessés et 3 surprises !|date=28 December 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=5 January 2024 |title=Côte D'Ivoire |url=https://www.cafonline.com/media/ow2obxrw/c%C3%B4te-divoire.pdf |publisher=Confederation of African Football}}</ref> On 11 February 2024, he came on as a late substitute in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations final|final]] of the tournament against [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]], which ended in a 2–1 victory for Ivory Coast.<ref name="2023caff">{{cite web|title=Nigeria 1–2 Ivory Coast: Sebastian Haller Grabs Winner as Hosts Win Africa Cup of Nations After Wild Tournament|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/africa-cup-of-nations/2024/nigeria-v-ivory-coast-afcon-final-live_sto10013363/story.shtml|publisher=[[Eurosport]]|date=11 February 2024|access-date=11 February 2024}}</ref>

Sangaré was included in the list of Ivorian players selected by coach [[Emerse Faé]] to participate in the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=Nicolas Pépé et Simon Adingra absents, Wilfried Zaha de retour : la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la CAN |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Nicolas-pepe-et-simon-adingra-absents-wilfried-zaha-de-retour-la-liste-de-la-cote-d-ivoire-pour-la-can/1615689 |website=www.lequipe.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=CAN 2025: la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire, tenante du titre, avec le retour de Wilfried Zaha |url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20251209-can-2025-la-liste-de-la-c%C3%B4te-d-ivoire-tenante-du-titre-avec-le-retour-de-wilfried-zaha |website=www.rfi.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On May 15, 2026, Sangaré was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Faé]] in his list of 26 players in order to participate in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

